    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_FixDatabaseTornPage",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to address and repair torn pages in a SQL Server database. Torn pages are a type of database corruption that can occur when a page write operation is interrupted, leaving the page in an inconsistent state. This procedure identifies torn pages, backs up the transaction log, restores the affected page from a backup, and then applies the transaction log to bring the database to a consistent state."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves several steps that require a good understanding of SQL Server backup and restore operations. It also requires knowledge of handling database corruption issues, making it moderately complex."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure does not take any input parameters. It operates on hardcoded database names and file paths, which limits its flexibility and requires manual modification for different databases or environments."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "orderedList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Identify Torn Pages",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure queries the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "msdb..suspect_pages",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table to find pages marked as torn ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "event_type = 3",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "). If no results are returned, there are no torn pages to fix."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Backup Transaction Log",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": It suggests backing up the transaction log of the affected database to ensure that no data is lost during the repair process. The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "BACKUP LOG",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " command is prepared but commented out, requiring manual intervention to specify the correct database name."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Restore Torn Page",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure includes a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "RESTORE DATABASE",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " command to restore the specific torn page from a backup file. The file ID and page ID need to be replaced with actual values obtained from the initial query."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Restore Transaction Log",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Finally, the procedure restores the transaction log to apply any changes that occurred after the backup, bringing the database to a consistent state."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Backup and Restore Operations",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": These operations can be resource-intensive and may impact database performance, especially on large databases or during peak usage times."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Disk I/O",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure involves reading from and writing to disk, which can be a bottleneck if the disk subsystem is not optimized for such operations."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Hardcoded Values",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure uses hardcoded database names and file paths, which can lead to errors if not updated correctly for each use case."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Loss",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the transaction log backup is not performed correctly, there is a risk of data loss."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Manual Intervention Required",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure requires manual updates to the database name and file paths, increasing the risk of human error."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Incomplete Recovery",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the backup files are not available or corrupted, the recovery process will fail, potentially leaving the database in an inconsistent state."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "No Error Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure lacks error handling, which means any failure during execution could leave the database in an unpredictable state without any notification or rollback mechanism."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "--Open and run in the query window\ncreate PROCEDURE [Utils].[usp_FixDatabaseTornPage]\r\nAS \r\nBEGIN   \r\n--Find the torn page. If no results returned then you are fine\r\nSELECT db_name(database_id) DatabaseName, file_id, page_id, last_update_date\r\nFROM msdb..suspect_pages\r\nWHERE event_type = 3\r\n\r\n--Backup your transaction log\r\n\r\n--USE master  -- Uncomment this when using\r\nBACKUP LOG DBName\r\nTO DISK = 'C:\\DBName.trn'\r\nWITH NORECOVERY\r\n\r\n--Restore Torn Page. 1 is the file_id, and 123 is the page_id from the first query\r\nRESTORE DATABASE DBName PAGE='1:123'\r\nFROM DISK='C:\\DBName.bak'\r\nWITH NORECOVERY\r\n\r\n\r\n--Restore your log\r\nRESTORE LOG DBName FROM\r\nDISK='C:\\DBName.trn'\r\nWITH RECOVERY\r\n\r\nEND"
        }
      ]
    }
